info.name: Post Label Center
info.description: This SOAP-based webservice enables direct interaction with the Post-Labelcenter for managing various shipment-related operations. It supports creating items, importing address data, cancelling shipments, and generating daily balances. All operations are executed via structured SOAP requests. When importing items, the response may include a label—either in PDF format or as a ZPL2 string—encoded as a Base64 string. These labels can be forwarded directly to a laser or label printer, depending on your system setup. The service is designed to integrate into logistics workflows, providing reliable functionality for operational teams handling high-volume shipping and label generation tasks.

item.name: Create Shipment

body.raw:
<soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" xmlns:post="http://post.ondot.at" xmlns:arr="http://schemas.microsoft.com/2003/10/Serialization/Arrays" xmlns:core="http://Core.Model" xmlns:ser="http://schemas.microsoft.com/2003/10/Serialization/">
    <soapenv:Header/>
    <soapenv:Body>
        <post:ImportShipmentAndGenerateBarcode>
            <post:row>
                <post:ClientID>{{plc_client_id}}</post:ClientID>
                <post:ColloList>
                    <post:ColloRow>
                        <post:Height>1</post:Height>
                        <post:Length>1</post:Length>
                        <post:Weight>1</post:Weight>
                        <post:Width>1</post:Width>
                    </post:ColloRow>
                </post:ColloList>
                <post:DeliveryServiceThirdPartyID>{{post_product_code}}</post:DeliveryServiceThirdPartyID>
                <post:OURecipientAddress>
                    <post:AddressLine1>Recipientstreet</post:AddressLine1>
                    <post:City>Wien</post:City>
                    <post:CountryID>AT</post:CountryID>
                    <post:Email/>
                    <post:HouseNumber>1</post:HouseNumber>
                    <post:Name1>Test Customer Name 1</post:Name1>
                    <post:Name2>Test Customer Name 2</post:Name2>
                    <post:PostalCode>1030</post:PostalCode>
                </post:OURecipientAddress>
                <post:OUShipperAddress>
                    <post:AddressLine1>Shipperstreet</post:AddressLine1>
                    <post:AddressLine2/>
                    <post:City>Wien</post:City>
                    <post:CountryID>AT</post:CountryID>
                    <post:Email/>
                    <post:HouseNumber>4</post:HouseNumber>
                    <post:Name1>Companyname TEMU</post:Name1>
                    <post:PostalCode>1220</post:PostalCode>
                    <post:Tel1/>
                </post:OUShipperAddress>
                <post:OUShipperReference1>{{external_shipper_reference}}</post:OUShipperReference1>
                <post:OrgUnitGuid>{{plc_org_unit_guid}}</post:OrgUnitGuid>
                <post:OrgUnitID>{{plc_org_unit_id}}</post:OrgUnitID>
                <post:PrinterObject>
                    <post:LabelFormatID>100x200</post:LabelFormatID>
                    <post:LanguageID>PDF</post:LanguageID>
                    <post:PaperLayoutID>A4</post:PaperLayoutID>
                </post:PrinterObject>
                <post:ShippingDateTimeFrom>{{$isoTimestamp}}</post:ShippingDateTimeFrom>
            </post:row>
        </post:ImportShipmentAndGenerateBarcode>
    </soapenv:Body>
</soapenv:Envelope>

request.description: Creates a shipment for Austria in the Post Label Center and returns the created label and an ident code.
